{{Quote|Stuart was already a makeup legend when he started on ''Star Wars''. He brought with him not only decades of experience, but boundless creative energy. His artistry and craftsmanship will live on forever in the characters he created. His ''Star Wars'' creatures may be reinterpreted in new forms by new generations, but at their heart, they continue to be what Stuart created for the original films.|George Lucas|<ref name="Remembered">{{SW|url=news/stuart-freeborn-remembered|text=Stuart Freeborn Remembered}}</ref>}}
'''Stuart Freeborn''' ([[September 5]], [[1910s#1914|1914]] &ndash; [[February 5]], [[2013]])<ref name="Lawless" /> was the makeup supervisor for the ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[original trilogy]]. He was hired by director [[George Lucas]] after Lucas became impressed with his makeup effects work in the [[1960s#1968|1968]] film [[Wikipedia:2001: A Space Odyssey (film)|''2001: A Space Odyssey'']].<ref name="The Art of Solo: A Star Wars Story">''[[The Art of Solo: A Star Wars Story]]''</ref> He worked on all three films and the [[The Star Wars Holiday Special|''Holiday Special'']].<ref name="Post">{{WebCite|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/style/longterm/movies/review97/starwarsarnold.htm|text='Star Wars' (PG)|author=Arnold, Gary|date=1977-05-25|Work=The Washington Post|archivedate=20200623173408}}</ref> Freeborn was responsible for transforming [[Peter Mayhew]] into [[Chewbacca]]. He was instructed to make a creature that was a mix of a [[Wikipedia:Dog|dog]] and a [[Wikipedia:Cat|cat]]. He was influenced by the monkey-man creatures that he worked on in ''2001: A Space Odyssey''.<ref name="Much to Learn">{{SW|url=news/much-to-learn-you-still-have-8-things-you-might-not-know-about-wookiees|text=Much to Learn You Still Have: 8 Things You Might Not Know About Wookiees}}</ref> Some of his most notable contributions include creatures at the [[Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina|Mos Eisley Cantina]],<ref name="Post" />[[Yoda]], Chewbacca, and [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure|Jabba]] the [[Hutt]].<ref name="Ultimate">''[[Ultimate Star Wars]]''</ref> He initially based Yoda's face on his own face, but he felt that those designs lacked the deep wisdom that Yoda deserved. He then combined his face that with [[Wikipedia:Albert Einstein|Albert Einstein's]] face.<ref name="Yoda Full Circle">{{SWKidsYouTube|series=Star Wars Full Circle|text=Yoda|video=qGo0Irzje3I|nolive=1}}</ref> His wife [[Kay Freeborn]] and son [[Graham Freeborn]] were also makeup artists.<ref name="Remembered" /> [[Orn Free Taa]] may have been named after him.<ref name="219 Tw'leks">{{InsiderCite|219|Day Wanna Wanga - The Tale of the Twi'leks}}</ref>

